8","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1173–1209":"1173–1209","1175–1217":"1175–1217","1187–1242":"1187–1242","1205–Male":"1205–Zesnulý","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1156–1211":"1156–1211","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","20 April 1208":"20. dubna 1208","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1211":"1211","1156":"1156","1209":"1209","1208":"1208","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, Anglie"},"da":{"1172–20 April 1208":"1172–20. april 1208","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1173–1209":"1173–1209","1175–1217":"1175–1217","1187–1242":"1187–1242","1205–Male":"1205–Afdød","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1156–1211":"1156–1211","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","20 April 1208":"20. april 1208","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1211":"1211","1156":"1156","1209":"1209","1208":"1208","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England"},"nl":{"1172–20 April 1208":"1172–20 april 1208","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1173–1209":"1173–1209","1175–1217":"1175–1217","1187–1242":"1187–1242","1205–Male":"1205–Overleden","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1156–1211":"1156–1211","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","20 April 1208":"20 april 1208","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1211":"1211","1156":"1156","1209":"1209","1208":"1208","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England"},"en":{"1172–20 April 1208":"1172–20 April 1208","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1173–1209":"1173–1209","1175–1217":"1175–1217","1187–1242":"1187–1242","1205–Male":"1205–Deceased","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1156–1211":"1156–1211","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","20 April 1208":"20 April 1208","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1211":"1211","1156":"1156","1209":"1209","1208":"1208","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hilton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire):","habitational name from any of various places called Hilton (e.g. in Cambridgeshire, Derbyshire, Staffordshire, North Yorkshire, and Westmorland), most of which derive from Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though some come from Old English <i>helde</i> ‘slope’ + <i>tūn</i>.","occasionally, as in the case of Ralph <i>filius Hilton</i> (Yorkshire 1219), perhaps from the personal name <i>Hilton</i>, itself a possible form of Norman <i>Hildun</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’ + <i>hūn</i> ‘bear cub’. Compare   Hilt  . This English surname is present in Ireland (mainly taken to Ulster in the early 17th century, though recorded earlier in Dublin)."],"variants":[{"name":"Hylton","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Hilton  ."]},{"name":"Hulton","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Hulton (Lancashire) or Hulton (Staffordshire), both from Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Hilton  ."]},{"name":"Hilt","meanings":["German: from a short form of   Hildebrand   or some other compound ancient Germanic name formed with <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’ as the first element. See   Hild  .","English (London): from the Middle English personal name <i>Hilte</i>, ultimately from ancient Germanic <i>Helto</i>, probably from <i>halith-</i> ‘hero’."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Hilton was born in 1172, in Hilton, Durham, England, his father, Alexander de Hilton, was 22 and his mother, Agnes de Vesci, was 16. He married Beneta Tyson in 1187, in Hilton, Durham, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 20 April 1208, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1172–20 April 1208":"1172–20. aprill 1208","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1173–1209":"1173–1209","1175–1217":"1175–1217","1187–1242":"1187–1242","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1156–1211":"1156–1211","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","20 April 1208":"20. aprill 1208","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1211":"1211","1156":"1156","1209":"1209","1208":"1208","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England"},"fi":{"1172–20 April 1208":"1172–20. huhtikuuta 1208","1172–1208":"1172–1208","1173–1209":"1173–1209","1175–1217":"1175–1217","1187–1242":"1187–1242","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1150–1197":"1150–1197","1156–1211":"1156–1211","1187":"1187","1242":"1242","1197":"119